comments.content: This pathway shows a apicoplast of the Plasmodium falciparum that infected a human cell. The human glycolysis provides the apicoplast with nutrients for its isoprenoid precursor biosynthesis. This pathway is being investigated for targets for malaria drug leads and drugs.
